1
00:00:05,548 --> 00:00:07,800
Then will you help with my ideas?

2
00:00:09,218 --> 00:00:12,513
I'd like you to make
bacon I can eat, Hank.

3
00:00:12,596 --> 00:00:15,307
- Bacon?!
- And I want Riyah to fly.

4
00:00:15,391 --> 00:00:16,559
Fly?!

5
00:00:16,642 --> 00:00:18,102
Of course I'll pay you.

6
00:00:18,185 --> 00:00:21,605
I think it's better than
wasting your time away, no?

7
00:00:24,150 --> 00:00:25,359
O-Okay.

8
00:00:25,443 --> 00:00:26,861
I'll do it, Kunon.

9
00:01:59,203 --> 00:02:00,204
FLYING AND ROASTING AND BEING INVITED

10
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:02,289
Here's my new giant hairless rat.

11
00:02:02,373 --> 00:02:05,084
For holding and going to sleep with?

12
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:06,168
Yes!

13
00:02:06,252 --> 00:02:08,671
I received feedback that
if the pillow is different,

14
00:02:08,754 --> 00:02:11,090
it can be harder to fall
asleep even on a water bed.

15
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:14,009
With this, you will fall
asleep no matter what.

16
00:02:14,093 --> 00:02:15,302
Would you like to try?

17
00:02:15,386 --> 00:02:20,015
I have a feeling I'll be obsessed
once I touch it, so I'll pass.

18
00:02:20,099 --> 00:02:21,517
Are you sure?

19
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,935
And you?

20
00:02:24,395 --> 00:02:26,564
I'll stay away as well.

21
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:28,274
Very well.

22
00:02:28,357 --> 00:02:32,528
My sleeping beauties await,
so please excuse me.

23
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:38,617
It seems to be going well.

24
00:02:38,701 --> 00:02:40,077
It's impressive.

25
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:43,956
He built such an efficient system
to make money in no time.

26
00:02:44,248 --> 00:02:45,833
Reyes is doing well, too.

27
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,587
Hank and Riyah have started their
experiments thanks to Kunon's advice.

28
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,755
Today marks one month
since they enrolled here.

29
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:55,301
I suppose we don't need
to supervise them anymore.

30
00:02:55,384 --> 00:02:58,888
A month, huh? Perhaps the
factions will make a move soon,

31
00:03:00,764 --> 00:03:02,224
Is Kunon here?

32
00:03:02,308 --> 00:03:04,143
I'd like to speak to him.

33
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:05,519
Me, too!

34
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:08,898
He just left.

35
00:03:09,148 --> 00:03:10,482
What?!

36
00:03:11,775 --> 00:03:13,485
Please excuse us.

37
00:03:14,403 --> 00:03:16,155
They're on the move.

38
00:03:16,238 --> 00:03:18,741
I can see a fierce battle already.

39
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:25,080
Now we have soft, smooth,
giant hairless rats.

40
00:03:25,164 --> 00:03:27,458
The perfect companion
for your peaceful sleep!

41
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:30,210
A 60-minute course with the add-on!

42
00:03:30,294 --> 00:03:31,921
I'll take a 90-minute course!

43
00:03:32,838 --> 00:03:34,924
The business is doing well as usual.

44
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:42,097
A-ori.

45
00:03:49,521 --> 00:03:51,190
You burned it again?

46
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:58,781
He's not here.

47
00:04:01,951 --> 00:04:04,161
Where did he go?

48
00:04:04,662 --> 00:04:06,705
Kunon?

49
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:12,920
I want you to make bacon
that can satisfy me soon.

50
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:17,383
I've never made bacon with
fire magic before, so...

51
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:22,012
Bacon is smoked for a long time,
rather than putting it on the fire.

52
00:04:22,304 --> 00:04:26,183
I think it's possible if you
can maintain a constant heat.

53
00:04:26,558 --> 00:04:28,602
I understand that,

54
00:04:28,686 --> 00:04:31,105
but maintaining it for a
long time is difficult.

55
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:33,816
What is it?

56
00:04:34,108 --> 00:04:35,484
Nothing.

57
00:04:35,651 --> 00:04:37,194
Then you've got to try again.

58
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:39,196
Fu-ra.

59
00:04:46,996 --> 00:04:48,247
Whoa!

60
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:50,666
Eek!

61
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:55,796
Kunon.

62
00:05:01,093 --> 00:05:03,721
Th-Thank you, Kunon.

63
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:07,182
You need to figure out how
to float with stability first.

64
00:05:07,266 --> 00:05:08,600
Right.

65
00:05:14,398 --> 00:05:16,066
Here are your sandwiches.

66
00:05:16,358 --> 00:05:19,236
The bacon's totally burnt...
Are you sure this is okay?

67
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:23,323
Yes. I can't let food go to waste.

68
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:27,244
You take responsibility
and eat these, too, Hank.

69
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,495
Sure.

70
00:05:29,121 --> 00:05:30,956
May I have some as well?

71
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:33,375
I want to save up as much money as I can.

72
00:05:33,459 --> 00:05:34,752
Of course.

73
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:38,672
Hank and I won't be able to finish
all these sandwiches ourselves.

74
00:05:42,426 --> 00:05:44,803
Hello, Miss Reyes.

75
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:53,395
I never imagined
you
would invite
me
to lunch!

76
00:05:53,479 --> 00:05:56,148
May I talk about how
moved I am all day long?

77
00:05:56,231 --> 00:05:57,941
No, thank you.

78
00:05:58,067 --> 00:06:02,946
I don't have to pay when I go to lunch
with you, so I'm grateful for that.

79
00:06:07,951 --> 00:06:10,537
This isn't... quite edible.

80
00:06:10,621 --> 00:06:13,207
I'm sorry, but can I leave the bacon?

81
00:06:15,459 --> 00:06:17,795
- Miss Reyes!
- Don't push yourself!

82
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:21,131
I'm sorry! I'm so ashamed!

83
00:06:25,177 --> 00:06:28,222
So we should've waited for
him here to begin with.

84
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:30,516
Looking all over for him like an idiot.

85
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:31,809
Who are you calling an idiot?

86
00:06:34,937 --> 00:06:36,230
Kunon.

87
00:06:36,313 --> 00:06:38,065
I just pulled an all-nighter.

88
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:39,733
Sell me good sleep, now!

89
00:06:39,817 --> 00:06:44,363
Thank you for requesting me,
my sleeping beauties and all of you.

90
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:46,323
Your Kunon has returned.

91
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:48,075
Oh, Kunon!

92
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:49,743
- I'm first!
- No, it's me!

93
00:06:49,827 --> 00:06:51,703
Hey, don't cut in line!

94
00:06:51,787 --> 00:06:54,414
I could collapse from
fatigue at any moment!

95
00:06:54,498 --> 00:06:56,208
Sorry.

96
00:07:02,131 --> 00:07:03,465
Thank you for waiting!

97
00:07:03,549 --> 00:07:04,633
Which course would you like?

98
00:07:04,716 --> 00:07:06,510
So the thing is, Kunon...

99
00:07:07,511 --> 00:07:09,054
What is this?

100
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,515
A sinful add-on for princesses
who are in need of cradles,

101
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:15,144
to whisk them away to even better sleep.

102
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:18,689
That water bed itself
provided a sanctuary.

103
00:07:19,106 --> 00:07:21,942
And now magic for even better rest...

104
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:25,362
What would you like to do?

105
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:28,073
There are three beds remaining.

106
00:07:28,157 --> 00:07:30,159
Giant hairless rat...

107
00:07:30,242 --> 00:07:31,535
I'm curious.

108
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:33,370
I want to try it.

109
00:07:48,343 --> 00:07:49,553
Ka-shi.

110
00:07:53,599 --> 00:07:55,893
It's easy to produce fire, but...

111
00:07:56,894 --> 00:08:00,397
I think it's possible if you
can maintain a constant heat.

112
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:02,649
Easy for you to say.

113
00:08:04,902 --> 00:08:07,613
Keep it low, keep it low.

114
00:08:14,328 --> 00:08:15,787
Go higher.

115
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:18,624
Higher.

116
00:08:20,209 --> 00:08:22,794
A new batch of shi-shilla, huh?

117
00:08:23,337 --> 00:08:28,217
Professor Sureyya was raving about
the quality of your previous report.

118
00:08:28,926 --> 00:08:30,761
- Professor.
- Yes?

119
00:08:31,303 --> 00:08:33,972
I'm still not convinced.

120
00:08:34,431 --> 00:08:39,186
Why is it necessary for us
to make money with magic?

121
00:08:41,647 --> 00:08:43,899
Ever since you were small,

122
00:08:43,982 --> 00:08:47,194
you all have only been doing experiments
and research on magic, right?

123
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:51,365
In society, there are
people who try to deceive

124
00:08:51,448 --> 00:08:54,701
and take advantage of
naive sorcerers like you.

125
00:08:55,744 --> 00:09:00,207
Magic is a special power given
only to the chosen people.

126
00:09:00,499 --> 00:09:03,961
Our job is to foster sorcerers
who can use that power correctly

127
00:09:04,086 --> 00:09:07,256
by making them work to
learn about society.

128
00:09:08,924 --> 00:09:11,218
Did that convince you?

129
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:13,220
Yes.

130
00:09:15,013 --> 00:09:17,224
Now it's Hank and Riyah's
turn to figure it out.

131
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,268
I hope it goes well for them.

132
00:09:19,351 --> 00:09:22,229
- They've got Kunon.
- What?

133
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:27,234
He's frivolous, but I'm sure
they'll learn a lot from him.

134
00:09:27,943 --> 00:09:29,278
Even though he's frivolous.

135
00:09:29,611 --> 00:09:30,737
You're right.

136
00:09:32,531 --> 00:09:36,535
Oh, recruiting for factions
has started today.

137
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:39,538
- Did anyone come to see you?
- No.

138
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:43,125
- No one? What about Kunon?
- No.

139
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,377
That's strange.

140
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,922
This is strange.

141
00:09:49,256 --> 00:09:54,219
No word from the students
I sent out for recruitment.

142
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:56,596
No need to rush.

143
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,056
It's only the first day.

144
00:09:58,140 --> 00:09:59,725
You're right.

145
00:10:07,149 --> 00:10:08,483
They're late.

146
00:10:19,828 --> 00:10:21,038
Factions?

147
00:10:21,663 --> 00:10:25,959
They're the organizations of the
students in the advanced class.

148
00:10:26,043 --> 00:10:30,964
Among them, the three largest factions
are Ability, Harmony, and Rationality.

149
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:35,886
Students in the advanced class are
treated as full-fledged sorcerers, right?

150
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:39,264
Professors don't intervene
more than necessary.

151
00:10:40,057 --> 00:10:42,434
So these are kind of like mutual
aid associations of students

152
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:44,061
who help each other when in need.

153
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:45,771
You know so much.

154
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:48,565
I used to be an assistant
to a professor here.

155
00:10:48,899 --> 00:10:51,234
I'm not too interested,

156
00:10:51,318 --> 00:10:53,779
since we're in a free environment and all.

157
00:10:54,237 --> 00:10:57,824
But there are experiments that
require lots of help, you know?

158
00:10:57,908 --> 00:11:01,036
Belonging to a faction
can be helpful then.

159
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:06,291
Doing experiments surrounded
by a lot of women, huh?

160
00:11:09,753 --> 00:11:11,505
Recruitment was forbidden

161
00:11:11,546 --> 00:11:15,592
for the first month so we
could get used to school life.

162
00:11:16,093 --> 00:11:19,054
Apparently yesterday was the opening day.

163
00:11:19,805 --> 00:11:22,057
Can we put in a request?

164
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:26,061
Yes. I'm thinking about joining Harmony.

165
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:28,480
I haven't picked one yet.

166
00:11:28,563 --> 00:11:30,899
I'm still not sure, either.

167
00:11:31,483 --> 00:11:35,487
Ability, Harmony, and Rationality, huh?

168
00:11:38,657 --> 00:11:41,660
Anyways, shall we eat today's bacon?

169
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:43,912
I didn't burn it today.

170
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:46,039
I roasted it slowly on a low heat.

171
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:48,166
Thank you for the food.

172
00:11:49,751 --> 00:11:51,294
It's so salty!

173
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:55,006
Why?! Was it the heat control?

174
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:57,676
You've gotta try again.

175
00:12:03,515 --> 00:12:07,352
What exactly did you do all day yesterday?

176
00:12:07,436 --> 00:12:09,771
I-I'm so sorry.

177
00:12:12,399 --> 00:12:14,192
Did that work?

178
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:18,405
Representative, that tone really suits you.

179
00:12:18,488 --> 00:12:19,948
Like a Demon Lord!

180
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:23,702
I'll have you know that this
is rather against my will.

181
00:12:24,411 --> 00:12:26,204
You couldn't recruit him?

182
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:28,623
I'm sorry, representative.

183
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:30,709
I fell asleep.

184
00:12:32,794 --> 00:12:35,672
You fell asleep...?

185
00:12:36,173 --> 00:12:39,759
I just couldn't resist his magic.

186
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:41,720
His giant hairless rat?

187
00:12:41,928 --> 00:12:43,638
His giant hairless rat.

188
00:12:43,972 --> 00:12:46,224
Oh, I see.

189
00:12:46,641 --> 00:12:51,730
As expected of Zeonly's student, I suppose.

190
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:07,537
Hello, Bael and Shilto.

191
00:13:07,621 --> 00:13:09,956
What brings you here?

192
00:13:10,332 --> 00:13:11,583
Stop acting so innocent.

193
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:15,045
Sorry, but I have no intention
of letting you go first.

194
00:13:15,337 --> 00:13:16,796
Same here.

195
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:23,762
Then shall we decide on the
order fair and square?

196
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:28,058
I'm so tired.

197
00:13:29,059 --> 00:13:31,895
Don't you want the incentive fee?
And the credits?

198
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:34,439
Way to prey on my vulnerability.

199
00:13:34,731 --> 00:13:36,274
If you ask me,

200
00:13:36,358 --> 00:13:41,446
I think you're the problematic one here,
trying to get paid for a half-baked job.

201
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:45,158
A critical hit with a fair argument.

202
00:13:45,242 --> 00:13:47,244
Fine, I'll do it.

203
00:13:48,245 --> 00:13:49,329
Fu-ra.

204
00:13:51,498 --> 00:13:53,333
How are you doing, Riyah?

205
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,585
I'm getting the hang of floating.

206
00:13:55,961 --> 00:13:58,672
Then let's try moving.

207
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:00,048
A-ori.

208
00:14:02,217 --> 00:14:05,637
Wow! Is this the same as the water bed?

209
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:08,265
Yes, because it's dangerous if you fall.

210
00:14:11,226 --> 00:14:15,313
There must be no water
Kunon can't produce.

211
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:20,068
Born to the house of a
baron in countryside,

212
00:14:20,402 --> 00:14:23,488
I was called the best
sorcerer in nation...

213
00:14:23,947 --> 00:14:24,990
Fu-garu.

214
00:14:27,576 --> 00:14:30,996
People thought I was a
future Royal Sorcerer,

215
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:33,290
but I was a big fish in a small pond.

216
00:14:33,665 --> 00:14:35,500
Shall we begin?

217
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:38,128
Are you ready, young man?

218
00:14:40,463 --> 00:14:43,842
For now, I have to be able to make money.

219
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:46,303
For the sake of my father who
scraped together the tuition for me,

220
00:14:46,386 --> 00:14:48,138
and my entire family.

221
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,307
Yeah, I'm ready!

222
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:54,769
I will record everything, from you
flying to falling and tumbling.

223
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:57,188
Don't write about me falling and tumbling.

224
00:14:57,272 --> 00:15:02,152
Okay, fine. I'll change that
to "he spoke to a girl."

225
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:05,113
Oh, then you can say I fell and tumbled.

226
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:11,661
Is that also a magic
experiment over there?

227
00:15:15,707 --> 00:15:20,712
He successfully completed the
school's assignment in a few tries.

228
00:15:20,795 --> 00:15:24,507
His skills are a better fit for
our Ability faction, I'd say!

229
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:32,349
I hear he has a capacity for teamwork,
giving advice to his classmates.

230
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:34,851
Harmony is the best fit for him!

231
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:41,107
Being a Hero's Scar, and given his
exceptional magic that even

232
00:15:41,191 --> 00:15:42,901
made Zeonly acknowledge
him as a student,

233
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:45,445
it's only rational that he
joins Rationality.

234
00:15:55,872 --> 00:15:58,083
That looks fun.

235
00:16:03,046 --> 00:16:04,297
Is it too weak?

236
00:16:05,173 --> 00:16:07,467
But high heat will burn it again.

237
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:09,469
Shall I keep it low?

238
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:14,224
So, high heat? High or low...?

239
00:16:14,599 --> 00:16:16,685
Are you going to leave it uncooked now?

240
00:16:16,768 --> 00:16:18,520
That's a boring failure.

241
00:16:18,603 --> 00:16:19,771
But this is fire.

242
00:16:19,854 --> 00:16:22,357
What else can I do other
than low or high heat?

243
00:16:22,774 --> 00:16:25,860
You were an assistant to a
professor for a long time, right?

244
00:16:26,277 --> 00:16:28,321
Yeah, and I was diligent.

245
00:16:28,405 --> 00:16:30,532
I learned the basics and
gained lots of knowledge.

246
00:16:30,615 --> 00:16:33,451
Then why aren't you
trying anything crafty?

247
00:16:33,535 --> 00:16:35,829
That's what I've been waiting for.

248
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:40,250
You're not an assistant anymore,
so you can let yourself be free.

249
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,628
Fire can have smell or different colors.

250
00:16:43,712 --> 00:16:47,924
What? Fire with smell and colors?

251
00:16:48,049 --> 00:16:50,176
Surprise me.

252
00:16:50,552 --> 00:16:53,430
Try every possible means and show
me your little magic tricks.

253
00:16:53,805 --> 00:16:56,349
I'm sure you can, Hank.

254
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:57,684
Hey, Kunon!

255
00:16:58,601 --> 00:17:01,938
Give that rat of yours
to this professor, stat!

256
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:06,443
My goodness. Why do you push yourself
until you get to this state?

257
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:09,904
But... my research...

258
00:17:09,988 --> 00:17:12,574
Understood! A-ori.

259
00:17:16,077 --> 00:17:17,412
Kunon!

260
00:17:17,871 --> 00:17:21,207
Is that what Zeonly taught you?

261
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:23,918
No, my first teacher.

262
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:28,506
She taught me that creativity
was a form of talent.

263
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:31,134
She yelled at me for calling
her magic "little tricks."

264
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,062
Magic is free, huh?

265
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,734
Fire of a different color...

266
00:17:54,491 --> 00:17:56,117
Fire with smell.

267
00:17:56,826 --> 00:17:58,620
A smell that fits bacon.

268
00:17:59,746 --> 00:18:01,247
Wood chips?

269
00:18:01,915 --> 00:18:03,124
No, hold on.

270
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:07,629
If I can add colors and
smells, why not flavors?

271
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:12,967
If I add flavor to the aroma of
herbs, it should work... Okay!

272
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:18,431
Oh, I see. This is how one experiments.

273
00:18:19,307 --> 00:18:21,559
I worked as an assistant
for so long that I forgot.

274
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:24,270
Experiments allow you to try many things.

275
00:18:24,521 --> 00:18:28,107
I've got to surprise him and
get the incentive fee.

276
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:30,193
Hey, Hank.

277
00:18:31,486 --> 00:18:33,863
Would you like to join Harmony?

278
00:18:34,656 --> 00:18:37,242
Whoa?!

279
00:18:40,662 --> 00:18:43,039
Stop, stop!

280
00:18:47,627 --> 00:18:51,130
Oh man, I fell and tumbled.

281
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:55,718
You lose balance because you're
trying to forcibly control the wind.

282
00:18:57,303 --> 00:19:02,058
Try doing it as if you're going along
with the wind, like you're following it.

283
00:19:03,268 --> 00:19:06,521
Th-Thank you very much.

284
00:19:13,194 --> 00:19:14,946
It's actually not bad.

285
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:19,951
Right. I like that it
has aroma and a flavor.

286
00:19:20,076 --> 00:19:21,870
You did it, Hank!

287
00:19:21,953 --> 00:19:23,079
Yes!

288
00:19:23,705 --> 00:19:29,377
It doesn't make me nauseous, and my body
doesn't reject it as a foreign object.

289
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:32,755
Let's keep this up and try
bacon of different meats.

290
00:19:32,839 --> 00:19:35,216
I knew you'd say that.

291
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:39,304
Bacon of fish, chicken, and mutton!

292
00:19:39,721 --> 00:19:41,806
You made all this, Hank?

293
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:43,933
Fish is my favorite.

294
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:45,310
This is incredible.

295
00:19:45,393 --> 00:19:46,519
You surprised me!

296
00:19:46,603 --> 00:19:49,480
- But I can't eat this much.
- Oops.

297
00:19:51,149 --> 00:19:54,319
At this quality, I'm happy
to purchase them from you.

298
00:19:54,402 --> 00:19:56,237
Looking forward to more tomorrow!

299
00:19:56,487 --> 00:19:58,531
Yes! Thank you very much!

300
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:04,412
Did you manage to fly, Riyah?

301
00:20:04,495 --> 00:20:08,333
Yes. I got advice from an
upperclassman in Rationality.

302
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,085
I can't fly too far yet, though.

303
00:20:11,419 --> 00:20:13,546
Once you can successfully
fly long distances,

304
00:20:13,671 --> 00:20:18,051
I think you can use it to
start a courier service.

305
00:20:18,384 --> 00:20:21,846
I see. That can be a business.

306
00:20:22,263 --> 00:20:24,641
Thank you, Kunon! I'll do my best!

307
00:20:25,099 --> 00:20:28,102
Of course! And let me
write a report on it!

308
00:20:30,813 --> 00:20:35,735
By the way, I was invited to join
Rationality when I got the advice.

309
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:39,447
And I think I'm going to do that.

310
00:20:39,989 --> 00:20:42,867
She was cute.

311
00:20:42,951 --> 00:20:45,328
I was invited to Harmony.

312
00:20:45,662 --> 00:20:50,750
I was invited to Ability,
but I'm not sure about it.

313
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:55,046
What? Then I'm the only one
who hasn't been invited.

314
00:20:55,296 --> 00:20:56,631
Oh.

315
00:20:56,714 --> 00:20:59,133
With you, Kunon...

316
00:20:59,217 --> 00:21:01,219
I think they're fighting over you.

317
00:21:01,302 --> 00:21:02,720
I think so, too.

318
00:21:03,054 --> 00:21:04,389
I agree.

319
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:09,477
Are you saying girls are fighting over me?

320
00:21:19,737 --> 00:21:24,742
The right of the first negotiation with
Kunon Gurion is the Ability faction's!

321
00:21:26,703 --> 00:21:28,871
Harmony will go second.

322
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:33,209
So Rationality goes third?

323
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,752
Very well.

324
00:21:35,044 --> 00:21:40,591
It does give you advantage to negotiate
first, but he's the one who chooses.

325
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:43,344
Lulu was at a disadvantage in
terms of his attributes.

326
00:21:43,428 --> 00:21:44,721
I feel bad you.

327
00:21:45,221 --> 00:21:48,808
I agreed to the conditions,
so I won't make excuse.

328
00:21:51,853 --> 00:21:55,440
You're on, the biggest boy
magnet of the faction.

329
00:21:55,523 --> 00:21:57,525
Sure thing, Mr. Bael!

330
00:23:40,962 --> 00:23:44,006
Next episode: "Fairies
Checking the Answer."
